This is true.  In the higher end mana regen is going to be more important than pure mana pool, so definitely consider getting some mana preservation and flowing thought items in your twinking ;-)  This is primarily the reason I focused on race abilities over race stats.<br>
<br>
I don't know much about Erudites and faction (I have heard its similar to Gnomish and Human starting factions.)  But I do know that outside of intelligence they don't convey any particular benefits to being one (outside of style/preference if you like them as a race.)  Similarly, humans being average aren't conveying many advantages, outside of good starting factions.<br>
<br>
High elves have infravision, which begins and ends their advantages IMHO.  Meanwhile Dark Elves and Gnomes have very good starting intelligence (both are quite respectable, although not as good as Erudites) but have advantages of not being night blind (intrinsic ultravision/infravision respectively) which is a nice perk.  Dark Elves get hide, which allows you to go AFK safely while medding in most places (just make sure you really are hidden) and I am told that Gnomish Tinkering is fun.<br>
<br>
